data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes `Func`, not `Expression<Func>`

Your manual expression tree won't compile. Replace it with the much simpler non-expression lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more `Expression.Lambda`, `Expression.Call`, etc.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one `Street` column (data corruption risk). EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). This will generate a migration that renames columns.

- **Nested full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix — pin the old names explicitly if you have an existing database:**

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street")); // keep sharing if intended
});

// For nested complex types, pin old convention:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City"); // old name without "Payment_"
```

Or, if the new names are fine, just generate a migration and apply it.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
